'''潜在有害程序'''（{{lang-en|Potentially unwanted program, '''PUP'''}}）<ref>{{cite web |title=DT科技评论第36期 |url=http://media.people.com.cn/GB/406559/412390/ |publisher=人民网 |accessdate=2019-01-11 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129202809/http://media.people.com.cn/GB/406559/412390/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>或'''潜在有害应用'''（{{lang-en|Potentially unwanted application, '''PUA'''}}）是用户可能认为不需要的[[软件|软件]]，通常在用户不知情或不愿意的情况下与用户想安装的软件一起被安装在用户的计算机上。在中国大陆，这类软件也被叫做'''捆绑软件'''和'''流氓软件'''。[[安全软件|安全软件]]或[[家长控制软件|家长控制软件]]会基于这类主观的标准进行定义。

这种软件可能会破坏用户用户隐私或计算机安全。软件提供者通常使用户下载目标程序的同时下载一个糖衣程序。然后在缺乏[[选择排除|选择排除]]的情况下，该程序可能在用户电脑上安装其他软件<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/36877160/ns/technology_and_science-tech_and_gadgets/t/facebook-evil-interface/|title=Facebook: The 'Evil Interface?'|work=msnbc.com|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2019-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717043306/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/36877160/ns/technology_and_science-tech_and_gadgets/t/facebook-evil-interface/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2010/04/facebooks-evil-interfaces|title=Facebook's "Evil Interfaces"|work=Electronic Frontier Foundation|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110114012/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2010/04/facebooks-evil-interfaces|dead-url=no}}</ref>，附加软件通常没有任何安装提示，也无法卸载或在安装时选择排除。<ref name="malwarebytes">{{Cite web|url=https://www.malwarebytes.org/pup/|title=Malwarebytes Potentially Unwanted Program Criteria|publisher=[[Malwarebytes|Malwarebytes]]|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2016-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409041138/https://www.malwarebytes.org/pup/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[杀毒软件|杀毒软件]]会把这些捆绑软件识别为潜在有害程序（PUP）<ref name="malwarebytes">{{Cite web|url=https://www.malwarebytes.org/pup/|title=Malwarebytes Potentially Unwanted Program Criteria|publisher=[[Malwarebytes|Malwarebytes]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/security/2009/12/av-comparatives-picks-eight-antipua-winners/|title=Rating the best anti-malware solutions|accessdate=28 January 2014|publisher=Arstechnica|archive-date=2014-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202092753/http://arstechnica.com/security/2009/12/av-comparatives-picks-eight-antipua-winners/|dead-url=no}}</ref>或潜在有害应用（PUA），包括广告软件，或向广告商出售用户网络活动的软件，向用户浏览的网页上加入自己的广告，使用高额短信服务向用户收费的软件。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://about-threats.trendmicro.com/us/archive/grayware/GENERIC_GRAYWARE|title=Threat Encyclopedia – Generic Grayware|accessdate=27 November 2012|publisher=Trend Micro|archive-date=2014-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714140157/http://about-threats.trendmicro.com/us/archive/grayware/GENERIC_GRAYWARE|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PUP Criteria">{{Cite web|title=PUP Criteria|accessdate=13 February 2015|publisher=Malwarebytes}}</ref>这些行为被广泛认为是不道德的，因为它们在没有用户知情的情况下危害了用户的[[计算机安全|计算机安全]]。

一些附加软件会在用户设备上安装[[根证书|根证书]]，从而使得黑客可以绕过浏览器警告拦截私人信息如银行账户信息。美国国土安全部建议用户清除一个不安全的根证书，因为他们会使用户暴露在严重的网络攻击下。<ref name="reutersdhs">{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/20/us-lenovo-cybersecurity-dhs-idUSKBN0LO21U20150220|title=U.S. government urges Lenovo customers to remove Superfish software|date=February 20, 2015|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=February 20, 2015|archive-date=2015-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220205408/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/20/us-lenovo-cybersecurity-dhs-idUSKBN0LO21U20150220|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

越来越多的开源软件项目表示，第三方网站在不通知项目组的情况下对他们的软件进行捆绑已经成为一个问题。几乎每个第三方免费软件下载网站都会在他们的下载中捆绑潜在附加软件(PUP)。<ref name="emisoft1">{{Cite web|url=http://blog.emsisoft.com/2015/03/11/mind-the-pup-top-download-portals-to-avoid/|title=Mind the PUP: Top download portals to avoid|accessdate=May 4, 2015|date=March 11, 2015|publisher=EMSISOFT|archive-date=2015-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150505040618/http://blog.emsisoft.com/2015/03/11/mind-the-pup-top-download-portals-to-avoid/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

软件开发者和安全专家建议人们只从官方网站上下载最新版，或从可信任的[[软件包管理系统|软件包管理系统]]或[[应用商店|应用商店]]下载程序。

== 来源 ==
历史上，首先利用'''潜在附加软件(PUP)'''制造利润的是美国的大公司们如[[Hotbar|Zango]]。在这些公司们被有关部门因为安装侵略性的有害的软件被调查后，这些行为减少了。<ref>[http://archive.omgn.com/nexus/?p=637 CDT Files Complaints Against Major Adware Distributor (archived)] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.omgn.com/nexus/?p=637 |date=20130825093842 }} January 27, 2006</ref>

=== Download Valley ===
致力于用捆绑'''潜在附加软件(PUP)'''来创造利润的企业们与Israeli软件公司们通常被叫做Download Valley。 这些公司们占有了很大一部分的软件下载安装工具市场<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3600064,00.html |title=3. |access-date=2016-05-11 |archive-date=2020-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202064753/https://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3600064,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，这些工具会往用户电脑上安装捆绑软件。这些公司几乎不受有关部门干扰。

== 附加软件 ==
近年，附加软件正在逐渐增多，2014年的一个研究显示24.77% 的[[恶意软件|恶意软件]]被分类成附加软件。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.emsisoft.com/2015/02/26/62-of-the-top-50-download-com-applications-bundle-toolbars-and-other-pups/|title=62% of the Top 50 Download.com applications bundle toolbars and other PUPs|date=26 Feb 2015|work=EMSISOFT blog|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2015-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150505075107/http://blog.emsisoft.com/2015/02/26/62-of-the-top-50-download-com-applications-bundle-toolbars-and-other-pups/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

很多软件包括附加的浏览器插件会记录用户的网络活动并向广告商出售这些信息，或在用户浏览的网页上插入广告<ref name="malwarebytes">{{Cite web|url=https://www.malwarebytes.org/pup/|title=Malwarebytes Potentially Unwanted Program Criteria|publisher=[[Malwarebytes|Malwarebytes]]}}</ref> 在Google拥有的网站的访问数据中，5%的浏览器访问被计算机程序注入了程序自己的广告。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en//pubs/archive/43346.pdf|title=Ad Injection at Scale: Assessing Deceptive Advertisement Modifications|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2015-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150605041757/https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en//pubs/archive/43346.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2920012/superfish-injects-ads-in-one-in-25-google-page-views.html |title=存档副本 |access-date=2016-05-11 |archive-date=2020-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027014317/https://www.pcworld.com/article/2920012/superfish-injects-ads-in-one-in-25-google-page-views.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cio.com.au/article/574450/superfish-injects-ads-one-25-google-page-views/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2016-05-11 |archive-date=2019-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211155152/https://www.cio.com.au/article/574450/superfish-injects-ads-one-25-google-page-views/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 研究人员筛选出了被用于广告注入的50,870个Google Chrome插件和34,407个程序。38%的插件和17%的程序被分类为[[恶意软件|恶意软件]]，其余的被分类为潜在附加广告程序。一些Google Chrome插件开发者把她们的插件出售给第三方公司，这些公司静默的推送附加更新使插件们变为广告程序。<ref name="ars-adwareacquire">{{Cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/security/2014/01/malware-vendors-buy-chrome-extensions-to-send-adware-filled-updates/|title=Adware vendors buy Chrome Extensions to send ad- and malware-filled updates|accessdate=20 January 2014|work=Ars Technica|archive-date=2014-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140120050522/http://arstechnica.com/security/2014/01/malware-vendors-buy-chrome-extensions-to-send-adware-filled-updates/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="wsj-chromeads">{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/01/19/google-removes-two-chrome-extensions-amid-ad-uproar/|title=Google Removes Two Chrome Extensions Amid Ad Uproar|accessdate=20 January 2014|work=Wall Street Journal|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727052154/https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/01/19/google-removes-two-chrome-extensions-amid-ad-uproar/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.schneier.com/blog/archives/2014/01/adware_vendors.html|title=Adware Vendors Buy and Abuse Chrome Extensions|author=Bruce Schneier|date=21 Jan 2014|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115120434/https://www.schneier.com/blog/archives/2014/01/adware_vendors.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 本地代理 ===
[[间谍软件|间谍软件]]会在用户的电脑上安装[[代理服务器|代理服务器]]以监控所有通过[[代理服务器|代理服务器]]的网络流量，分析这些流量，提取用户特征并把它们出售给广告商。

==== Superfish ====
[[Superfish|Superfish]]是一个广告注入软件，它会在系统中生成自己的[[根证书|根证书]]使得该软件可以在加密的谷歌搜索结果中插入广告并监视用户的搜索结果。

2015年1月，[[美國國土安全部|美國國土安全部]]建议用户卸载Superfish和与它相关的[[根证书|根证书]]，因为他们会使用户暴露在严重的网络攻击下，这些攻击包括拦截通过浏览器传输的用户密码和敏感数据。<ref name="reutersdhs">{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/20/us-lenovo-cybersecurity-dhs-idUSKBN0LO21U20150220|title=U.S. government urges Lenovo customers to remove Superfish software|date=February 20, 2015|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.us-cert.gov/ncas/alerts/TA15-051A|title=Alert: Lenovo "Superfish" Adware Vulnerable to HTTPS Spoofing|accessdate=February 20, 2015|date=February 20, 2015|publisher=United States Computer Emergency Readiness Team|archive-date=2017-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820211239/https://www.us-cert.gov/ncas/alerts/TA15-051A|dead-url=no}}</ref> {{tsl|en|Heinz Heise|Heise Security}} 在SAY Media和Lavasoft等公司的广告软件的中发现被捆绑在其中的Superfish的证书。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://heise.de/-2557619|title=Gefährliche Adware: Mehr als ein Dutzend Anwendungen verbreiten Superfish-Zertifikat|accessdate=May 5, 2015|date=February 24, 2015|work={{tsl|en|Heinz Heise|Heise Security}}|trans_title=Dangerous Aware: More than a Dozen Applications spreading Superfish Certificate}}</ref>

=== 浏览器劫持 ===
很多公司使用[[浏览器劫持|浏览器劫持]]来更改用户的首页和搜索页以增加特定网站的点击量并通过广告赚取利润<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.codeword.xyz/2015/08/09/exploiting-android-users-for-fun-and-profit/|title=Exploiting Android Users for Fun and Profit|author=Rudis Muiznieks|work=The Code Word|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611120345/https://www.codeword.xyz/2015/08/09/exploiting-android-users-for-fun-and-profit/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一些公司盗取用户浏览器中的cookies信息，[[会话劫持|劫持]]他们到网站的网络连接，并在不通知用户的情况下用用户的账号进行操作（比如安装[[Android|Android]]应用）。

=== 欺诈拨号 ===
一些用户使用[[撥號連線|拨号连接]]通过[[调制解调器|调制解调器]]访问互联网，这些用户成为了欺诈软件的目标，它们使用[[操作系统|操作系统]]中的[[计算机安全隐患|安全漏洞]]来向收费电话拨号。

很多[[Android|Android]]设备成为了恶意软件的目标，它们使用收费短信服务并向用户收费。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scmagazine.com/android-trojan-sends-premium-sms-messages-targets-us-users-for-first-time/article/343953/|title=Android trojan sends premium SMS messages, targets U.S. users for first time|work=SC Magazine|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2016-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624185722/http://www.scmagazine.com/android-trojan-sends-premium-sms-messages-targets-us-users-for-first-time/article/343953/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pandasecurity.com/mediacenter/malware/new-malware-attack-through-google-play/|title=New malware attack through Google Play|work=MediaCenter Panda Security|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926214608/https://www.pandasecurity.com/mediacenter/malware/new-malware-attack-through-google-play/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehackernews.com/2014/02/android-Malware-subscription-premium-SMS-Services.html|title=300000 Android Devices infected by Premium SMS-Sending Malware|author=Swati Khandelwal|date=15 February 2014|work=The Hacker News - Biggest Information Security Channel|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228192511/https://thehackernews.com/2014/02/android-Malware-subscription-premium-SMS-Services.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 第三方网站 ==
2015年, 一个来自EMSISOFT的研究指出，所有免费下载网站在它们的下载中捆绑潜在附加软件，Download.com被指为“最差分子”<ref name="emisoft1">{{Cite web|url=http://blog.emsisoft.com/2015/03/11/mind-the-pup-top-download-portals-to-avoid/|title=Mind the PUP: Top download portals to avoid|accessdate=May 4, 2015|date=March 11, 2015|publisher=EMSISOFT}}</ref> Lowell Heddings表达了他的沮丧："''Sadly, even on Google all the top results for most open source and freeware are just ads for really terrible sites that are bundling crapware, [[廣告軟體|adware]], and [[恶意软件|malware]] on top of the installer''."<ref name="howtogeek">{{Cite web|url=http://www.howtogeek.com/207692/yes-every-freeware-download-site-is-serving-crapware-heres-the-proof/|title=Yes, Every Freeware Download Site is Serving Crapware (Here’s the Proof)|date=21 Jan 2015|work=HowToGeek.com|quote=Sadly, even on Google all the top results for most open source and freeware are just ads for really terrible sites that are bundling crapware, adware, and malware on top of the installer. Most geeks will know that they shouldn’t click on the ads, but obviously enough people are clicking those ads for them to be able to afford to pay the high per-click prices for Google AdWords.|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211107190840/https://www.howtogeek.com/207692/yes-every-freeware-download-site-is-serving-crapware-heres-the-proof/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== Download.com ===
2011年12月，[[Download.com|Download.com]]开始在他们的软件中捆绑潜在附加软件，Gordon Lyon对Download.com的做法表示强烈厌恶并对这些捆绑软件表示担忧。Gordon Lyon的文章被很多人在社交网络上传播，并引起了几十个媒体报道。主要的问题集中在Download.com提供的内容<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2011/12/download-com-bundling-toolbars-trojans/|title=Download.com Bundling Toolbars, Trojans?|accessdate=2015-05-04|author=Brian Krebs|date=2011-12-06|authorlink=Brian Krebs|work=Krebs on security|archive-date=2021-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104141643/https://krebsonsecurity.com/2011/12/download-com-bundling-toolbars-trojans/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="insecure">{{Cite web|url=http://insecure.org/news/download-com-fiasco.html#exec|title=Download.com Caught Adding Malware to Nmap & Other Software|accessdate=2015-05-04|author=Gordon Lyon|date=2012-06-27|authorlink=Gordon Lyon|quote=we suggest avoiding CNET Download.com entirely|archive-date=2022-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107104719/https://insecure.org/news/download-com-fiasco.html#exec|dead-url=no}}</ref> 和原作者创作的软件的不同上；对Download.com的指责包括欺骗和版权与商标侵权。<ref name="insecure">{{Cite web|url=http://insecure.org/news/download-com-fiasco.html#exec|title=Download.com Caught Adding Malware to Nmap & Other Software|accessdate=2015-05-04|author=Gordon Lyon|date=2012-06-27|authorlink=Gordon Lyon|quote=we suggest avoiding CNET Download.com entirely}}</ref>

2014年，The Register和US-CERT警告用户：download.com的 "''foistware''"使"''attacker may be able to download and execute arbitrary code''".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theregister.co.uk/2014/07/08/download_wrappers_spruiked_vulnerable_avg_tool_cert_us_warns/|title=Insecure AVG search tool shoved down users' throats, says US CERT|accessdate=2015-05-04|author=Darren Pauli|date=2014-07-08|publisher=The Register|quote=Sneaky 'foistware' downloads install things you never asked for|archive-date=2019-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211152705/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2014/07/08/download_wrappers_spruiked_vulnerable_avg_tool_cert_us_warns/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== Sourceforge ===
很多[[开源软件|开源软件]]开发者对打包他们的软件并用他们的软件赚取广告费（它们总能占据搜索引擎的第一位）的公司们的行为表示挫败与沮丧。这些网站越来越多的在下载中使用被捆绑的安装器，其中就包括 潜在附加软件，并让捆绑软件看起来像是开发者背书的官方下载页面。

==== GIMP ====
2013年11月，[[GIMP|GIMP]]，一个免费图像编辑软件，因为[[SourceForge|SourceForge]]上的误导性的下载按钮与进行捆绑安装的SourceForge Windows安装器，其开发者从[[SourceForge|SourceForge]]移除了它的下载链接。与之相比，GIMP的开发者曾经认为SourceForge是一个"''useful and trustworthy place to develop and host FLOSS applications''"，他们现在面临"''a problem with the ads they allow on their sites ...''"<ref name="Register: Gimp departs SourceForge">{{Cite news|url=http://www.theregister.co.uk/2013/11/08/gimp_dumps_sourceforge_over_dodgy_ads_and_installer/|title=GIMP flees SourceForge over dodgy ads and installer|last=Sharwood|first=Simon|date=November 8, 2013|newspaper=The Register|accessdate=November 21, 2013|archive-date=2020-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501025909/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2013/11/08/gimp_dumps_sourceforge_over_dodgy_ads_and_installer/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2015年5月,GIMP的Windows版SourceForge项目的所有权被转移到"SourceForge Editorial Staff" 账号并且广告软件下载按钮被恢复。<ref name="ars-gimpwindowssf">{{Cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/06/sourceforge-locked-in-projects-of-fleeing-users-cashed-in-on-malvertising/|title=SourceForge locked in projects of fleeing users, cashed in on malvertising|accessdate=2 June 2015|website=Ars Technica|archive-date=2015-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150602181536/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/06/sourceforge-locked-in-projects-of-fleeing-users-cashed-in-on-malvertising/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 同样的事情发生在[[nmap|nmap]]的开发者身上。<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=http://seclists.org/nmap-dev/2015/q2/194|title=Sourceforge Hijacks the Nmap Sourceforge Account|date=3 June 2015|work=Seclists.org|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419015151/https://seclists.org/nmap-dev/2015/q2/194|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{Cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/06/black-mirror-sourceforge-has-now-siezed-nmap-audit-tool-project/|title=Black "mirror": SourceForge has now seized Nmap audit tool project|author=Sean Gallagher|date=4 June 2015|work=Ars Technica|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2017-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708075056/https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/06/black-mirror-sourceforge-has-now-siezed-nmap-audit-tool-project/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年5月，SourceForge取走了一些移到其他代码托管网站的开源项目的管理权限并把项目的下载链接换成广告程序的下载链接。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/05/sourceforge-grabs-gimp-for-windows-account-wraps-installer-in-bundle-pushing-adware/|title=SourceForge grabs GIMP for Windows’ account, wraps installer in bundle-pushing adware [Updated]|accessdate=2015-05-30|archive-date=2016-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505131345/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/05/sourceforge-grabs-gimp-for-windows-account-wraps-installer-in-bundle-pushing-adware/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

